DataElement.preferredName: Breast Cancer TNM Finding Metastasis Anatomic Site java.util.Collection
DataElement.preferredDefinition: definition pending_Metastasis is the spread or migration of cancer cells from one part of the body (the organ in which it first appeared) to another. The secondary tumor contains cells that are like those in the original (primary) tumor. For example, breast cancer cells may spread (metastasize) to the lungs and cause the growth of a new tumor. When this happens, the disease is called metastatic breast cancer. (NCI):Named locations of, or within, the body._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is defined as a group of objects.
